      "translationId": "BSB"
    },
    "chapter": {
      "content": [
        {
          "content": [
            "The Descendants of Adam"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "This is the book of the generations of Adam. In the day that God created man, He made him in His own likeness."
          ],
          "number": 1,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Male and female He created them,",
            {
              "noteId": 4341
            },
            "and He blessed them. And in the day they were created, He called them “man.”",
            {
              "noteId": 4342
            }
          ],
          "number": 2,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Adam was 130 years old, he had a son in his own likeness, after his own image; and he named him Seth."
          ],
          "number": 3,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Seth, Adam lived 800 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 4,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Adam lived a total of 930 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 5,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Seth was 105 years old, he became the father of Enosh."
          ],
          "number": 6,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Enosh, Seth lived 807 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 7,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Seth lived a total of 912 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 8,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Enosh was 90 years old, he became the father of Kenan."
          ],
          "number": 9,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Kenan, Enosh lived 815 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 10,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Enosh lived a total of 905 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 11,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Kenan was 70 years old, he became the father of Mahalalel."
          ],
          "number": 12,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Mahalalel, Kenan lived 840 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 13,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Kenan lived a total of 910 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 14,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Mahalalel was 65 years old, he became the father of Jared."
          ],
          "number": 15,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Jared, Mahalalel lived 830 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 16,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Mahalalel lived a total of 895 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 17,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "God Takes Up Enoch"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Jared was 162 years old, he became the father of Enoch."
          ],
          "number": 18,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Enoch, Jared lived 800 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 19,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Jared lived a total of 962 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 20,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Enoch was 65 years old, he became the father of Methuselah."
          ],
          "number": 21,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Methuselah, Enoch walked with God",
            {
              "noteId": 4343
            },
            "300 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 22,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Enoch lived a total of 365 years."
          ],
          "number": 23,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Enoch walked with God, and then he was no more, because God had taken him away.",
            {
              "noteId": 4344
            }
          ],
          "number": 24,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "From Methuselah to Noah"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Methuselah was 187 years old, he became the father of Lamech."
          ],
          "number": 25,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Lamech, Methuselah lived 782 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 26,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Methuselah lived a total of 969 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 27,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When Lamech was 182 years old, he had a son."
          ],
          "number": 28,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And he named him Noah,",
            {
              "noteId": 4345
            },
            "saying, “May this one comfort us in the labor and toil of our hands caused by the ground that the LORD has cursed.”"
          ],
          "number": 29,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And after he had become the father of Noah, Lamech lived 595 years and had other sons and daughters."
          ],
          "number": 30,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Lamech lived a total of 777 years, and then he died."
          ],
          "number": 31,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "After Noah was 500 years old, he became the father of Shem, Ham, and Japheth."
          ],
          "number": 32,
          "type": "verse"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4341,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 5,
            "verse": 2
          },
          "text": "Cited in Matthew 19:4 and Mark 10:6"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4342,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 5,
            "verse": 2
          },
          "text": "Hebrew Adam"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4343,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 5,
            "verse": 22
          },
          "text": "LXX pleased God; also in verse 24"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4344,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 5,
            "verse": 24
          },
          "text": "LXX and he was not found, because God had taken him away; cited in Hebrews 11:5"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4345,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 5,
            "verse": 29
          },
          "text": "Noah sounds like the Hebrew for rest or comfort."
        }
      ],
      "number": 5
    },
